Survival analysis by immune cells

This notebook will do the following multivariate survival analyses: 1. Multivariate analysis using immune cell types (minus uncharacterized), PDL1 expression, and cancer group as covariates 2. Multivariate analysis for each cancer group, using immune cell types (minus uncharacterized), PDL1 expression, and molecular subtype as covariates

Establish directories

# define directories
root_dir <- rprojroot::find_root(rprojroot::has_dir(".git"))
data_dir <- file.path(root_dir, "data")
input_dir <- file.path(root_dir, "analyses", "immune-deconv")
analysis_dir <- file.path(root_dir, "analyses", "survival-analysis")

results_dir <- file.path(analysis_dir, "results")
if(!dir.exists(results_dir)){
  dir.create(results_dir)
}

Read in required files

# Read in analysis data
quantiseq <- readRDS(file.path(input_dir, "results", "quantiseq_deconv-output.rds")) %>%
  # remove uncharacterized
  dplyr::filter(cell_type != "uncharacterized cell")
polya <- readRDS(file.path(data_dir, "pbta-gene-expression-rsem-fpkm-collapsed.polya.rds"))
stranded <- readRDS(file.path(data_dir, "pbta-gene-expression-rsem-fpkm-collapsed.stranded.rds"))

# Read in histology file
histology_df <- readr::read_tsv(file.path(data_dir, "pbta-histologies.tsv"))
Parsed with column specification:
cols(
  .default = col_character(),
  OS_days = col_double(),
  age_last_update_days = col_double(),
  normal_fraction = col_double(),
  tumor_fraction = col_double(),
  tumor_ploidy = col_double()
)
See spec(...) for full column specifications.

filter to cancer group of interest

# define cancer group of interest
cancer_groups_of_interest <- c("High-grade glioma astrocytoma", 
                              "Diffuse midline glioma",
                              "Low-grade glioma astrocytoma", 
                              "Ependymoma", 
                              "Medulloblastoma")

# filter to cancer group of interest 
histologies_df_filtered <- histology_df %>%
  # RNA-Seq samples only
  dplyr::filter(experimental_strategy == "RNA-Seq",
                composition=="Solid Tissue",
                tumor_descriptor == "Initial CNS Tumor",
                cancer_group %in% cancer_groups_of_interest) %>%
  dplyr::select(Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID, Kids_First_Participant_ID, cancer_group, OS_status, OS_days, molecular_subtype) %>%
  distinct() %>%
  dplyr::arrange(Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID)

Add immune information

# filter to samples of interest
quantiseq_subset <- quantiseq %>%
  dplyr::filter(sample %in% histologies_df_filtered$Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(cell_type_modi = gsub(" ", "_", cell_type),
                cell_type_modi = gsub("\\+", "", cell_type_modi),
                cell_type_modi = gsub("\\(", "", cell_type_modi),
                cell_type_modi = gsub("\\)", "", cell_type_modi),
                cell_type_modi = gsub("\\-", "_", cell_type_modi)) %>%
  dplyr::mutate() %>%
  dplyr::select(-cell_type)

# spread the results
quantiseq_subset_spread <- quantiseq_subset %>%
  tidyr::spread(cell_type_modi, score) %>%
  dplyr::rename(Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID = sample) %>%
  dplyr::left_join(histologies_df_filtered) %>%
  dplyr::select(-method)
Joining, by = "Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID"

Add RNA-Seq expression

# get poly-A samples
polya_samples <- quantiseq_subset_spread %>%
  dplyr::filter(library == "polya") %>%
  pull(Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID)

# get stranded samples
stranded_samples <- quantiseq_subset_spread %>%
  dplyr::filter(library == "stranded") %>%
  pull(Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID)

# get CD274 expression for polya
polya_cd274 <- polya %>%
  dplyr::select(all_of(polya_samples)) %>%
  tibble::rownames_to_column("gene_symbol") %>%
  dplyr::filter(gene_symbol == "CD274") %>%
  tibble::column_to_rownames("gene_symbol") %>% 
  t() %>% as.data.frame() %>%
  tibble::rownames_to_column("Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID")

# get CD274 expression for stranded
stranded_cd274 <- stranded %>%
  dplyr::select(all_of(stranded_samples)) %>%
  tibble::rownames_to_column("gene_symbol") %>%
  dplyr::filter(gene_symbol == "CD274") %>%
  tibble::column_to_rownames("gene_symbol") %>% 
  t() %>% as.data.frame() %>%
  tibble::rownames_to_column("Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID")
  
# combine stranded and polya
combined_cd274 <- bind_rows(polya_cd274, stranded_cd274)

# add expression to quantiseq results
combined_df <- quantiseq_subset_spread %>%
  dplyr::left_join(combined_cd274)
Joining, by = "Kids_First_Biospecimen_ID"

get distinct sample

# get distinct results 
combined_df_distinct <- combined_df %>%
  dplyr::distinct(Kids_First_Participant_ID, .keep_all=TRUE) %>%
  # recode the categories - 
  # DECEASED maps to a survival event status of 1, LIVING maps to a censored observation with value 0
  dplyr::mutate(OS_status_fixed = case_when(
    OS_status == "LIVING" ~ 0,
    OS_status == "DECEASED" ~1
 )) %>% 
  dplyr::mutate(OS_years = OS_days / 365.25)

Run multivariate analysis for all cancer groups

# find all immune cell types 
immune_cells <- quantiseq_subset %>% pull(cell_type_modi) %>% unique() %>%
  paste0(collapse = "+")

# define model
model <- paste0("survival::Surv(time = OS_years, event = OS_status_fixed) ~ ",
                immune_cells, 
                "+cancer_group+CD274")

fit <- survival::coxph(formula(model),
                       data = combined_df_distinct)
# generate output
table <- broom::tidy(fit) 

# Save the table data in a TSV
readr::write_tsv(table, file.path(results_dir, "cox_reg_results_5cgs.tsv"))

print(table)

Run multivariate analysis for each cancer group with gene expression and immune cells are covariates

for(cg_each in cancer_groups_of_interest){
  # filter to the cancer group of interset 
  combined_df_distinct_each <- combined_df_distinct %>%
    dplyr::filter(cancer_group == cg_each)
      # define model
  model <- paste0("survival::Surv(time = OS_years, event = OS_status_fixed) ~ ",
                  immune_cells, 
                  "+CD274")
  
  fit <- survival::coxph(formula(model),
                         data = combined_df_distinct)
  # generate output
  table <- broom::tidy(fit) 
  
  # Save the table data in a TSV
  readr::write_tsv(table, file.path(results_dir, paste0("cox_reg_results_in_", cg_each, ".tsv")))
  print(table)
  
  # printout the plot
  forest_coxph <- survminer::ggforest(fit, data = combined_df_distinct)
  print(forest_coxph)
}

Run multivariate analysis for individual cancer group parsed by molecular subtype

for(cg_each in c("Diffuse midline glioma")){
  # filter to the cancer group of interset 
  combined_df_distinct_each <- combined_df_distinct %>%
    dplyr::filter(cancer_group == cg_each)
  
  # define model
  model <- paste0("survival::Surv(time = OS_years, event = OS_status_fixed) ~ ",
                  immune_cells, 
                  "+molecular_subtype+CD274")
  
  fit <- survival::coxph(formula(model),
                         data = combined_df_distinct_each)
  # generate output
  # print(summary(fit))
  table <- broom::tidy(fit)
  
  # to avoid not being able to generate figures, we have to remove the covariates that have Inf
  valid_non_subtype <- table %>%
    # get non subtype covariates
    dplyr::filter(!grepl("molecular_subtype", term)) %>%
    # filter out infinite covariates
    dplyr::filter(!is.infinite(conf.low),
                  !is.infinite(conf.high)) %>%
    dplyr::filter(!is.na(statistic)) %>%
    # get the terms
    pull(term)

  # we have to filter out subtypes that are infinite
  subtypes_inf <- table %>%
    # get non subtype covariates
    dplyr::filter(grepl("molecular_subtype", term)) %>%
    dplyr::filter(is.infinite(conf.low) |
                  is.infinite(conf.high)) %>%
    dplyr::filter(!is.na(statistic)) %>%
    dplyr::mutate(term = gsub("molecular_subtype", "", term)) %>%
    pull(term)

  # filter out dataframe
  combined_df_distinct_each_filtered <- combined_df_distinct_each %>%
    dplyr::filter(!molecular_subtype %in% subtypes_inf)

  # build a model with just the valid covariate
  valid_non_subtype_formula <- valid_non_subtype %>% paste0(collapse = "+")

  # define model
  model <- paste0("survival::Surv(time = OS_years, event = OS_status_fixed) ~ ",
                  valid_non_subtype_formula,
                  "+molecular_subtype")

  fit_new <- survival::coxph(formula(model),
                         data = combined_df_distinct_each_filtered)
  # # generate output
  # print(summary(fit_new))
  # printout the plot
  forest_coxph <- survminer::ggforest(fit_new, data = combined_df_distinct_each_filtered)
  print(forest_coxph)
}
